article.headline: Oral Roberts 74, Centenary 53
article.story: TULSA, Okla. (AP) -- Larry Owens had 19 points and nine rebounds to lead Oral Roberts past Centenary 74-53 in a Mid-Continent Conference game on Thursday night. Moses Ehambe, who had four 3-pointers, added a season-high 14 points for ORU (11-9, 6-2 Mid-Con). Caleb Green also scored 14 points for the Golden Eagles. Alexander Starr was 7-of-11 from the field as he paced the Gents (4-15, 2-6) with 15 points. The Golden Eagles went on a 13-0 run in the final 7:40 of the first half to take a 34-24 lead at intermission. Owens had eight points and an assist during that stretch. Centenary outscored ORU 8-3 in the first three minutes of the second half to cut its deficit to 37-32. An Owens dunk then ignited a 7-0 ORU run and Centenary never got closer than eight points again. ORU sealed the outcome with a 15-2 spurt midway through the second half to stretch its lead to 61-40. The biggest ORU lead was at 65-43 with 5:54 left. After ORU scored the first two baskets of the game, Centenary answered with a 14-2 roll for a 14-6 lead. Xavier Burnette scored eight of his 11 points during that span. The Golden Eagles countered with 12 straight points, capped by two treys by Ehambe, to jump ahead 16-14. Consecutive baskets by Larry Logan and Chris Watson gave Centenary its last lead at 24-21.
